================ SCION Playground — AS 1-{{ playground_as }} ================
You are an endhost inside AS 1-{{ playground_as }} of the IETF testbed.
Try these, and watch the dashboard map react:

  scion showpaths 1-150 --extended     # paths to a core AS
  scion ping 1-150,10.20.3.150         # ping a border router in AS 1-150
  scion traceroute 1-153,10.20.3.153
  hev3 https://web.scion/              # Happy Eyeballs v3: SCION vs IPv6 vs IPv4 race
  hev3 --no-ip -k 3 https://web.scion/ # SCION multipath (shape a link -> watch failover)
  scapy-scion                          # SCION-aware scapy (raw sockets enabled)

This testbed also runs plain BGP/IP over the SAME links (compare the planes!):
  traceroute as153.scion               # hops show per-AS anchors (as150..as161)
  ping as150.scion                     # or web.scion / web2.scion
  mtr as150.scion                      # live per-hop latency (shape a link, watch it move)
  tcpdump -ni eth0 icmp                # no root needed; watch your own packets

Endhost ASes you can join with your laptop: 1-152, 1-155, 1-158, 1-161.
Session is sandboxed and resets on disconnect. Have fun!
